College Football Coaches, The Ultimate 1 Percent
December 29, 2014
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~=
~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~=
~~~~~

College football coaches love to compete, nowhere more so than in their sal=
aries.
Alabama's Nick Saban, whose Crimson Tide plays Ohio State in the Sugar Bowl=
 this
 New Years's Day, pulls in $6.9 million a year, giving him bragging rights =
as the
highest-paid coach in college football. That is, until Jim Harbaugh takes o=
ver as
coach of the University of Michigan Wolverines next year for a reported $7 =
million
annual salary.
How can public universities afford such obscene compensation? One big reaso=
n is=20
that they pay their players nothing. Indeed, while Saban and his ilk enjoy =
ever-swelling
salaries, bonuses, paid media appearances, and other perks like free housin=
g, college
players must endure draconian NCAA rules that banish them to hell for such =
sins=20
as signing an autograph for cash or selling a jersey, all in the name of pr=
otecting
the "amateur" spirit of the game.
But as Matt Connolly shows in a sneak preview  [http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=
=3D0014uSVjVqKX26t3fK3-Wyr7DSs7Nms4sjJcFdvmFUb0RLKuQsrooEDIro0UaARwlgq-Mnik=
b7AOJD7IYRJWuNCjTLwVYwVjljWqEZHvk6tgMKJ4ZXjgvl5Yl8K6c9i__AO86obPax1fDELUg7O=
R60s6rxui6HXBJHJioAkLkbD2VDeBUVr0Knphocq0cRAai81DB2RHCGPqFbtoqgHMvzkwSxdHHZ=
xcouuIkvP3QBt0mHq7ARmlbBmEHL-tcnlHShodU8Ofmpi2W_BCaA0sNmfNRdymFK4TOgdontHmC=
5YXF8ljQbYTAxNjg=3D=3D&c=3D699CB-aJs7hzG9fER7myR7tSGRYASEx2U8Af6YlaaXlEfCLA=
Kk83Ug=3D=3D&ch=3D3kpueLkEHLaFUbrp4THBWEB12DltJFHOOk-wlMeR6JVco7I99gT-Ow=3D=
=3D]
from the upcoming the January/February issue of the Washington Monthly, the=
re was
a time, more than a century ago, when college teams didn't pay their coache=
s, either.
The arguments back then against compensating coaches looked surprisingly si=
milar
 to the arguments today against paying players.
Read "College Football Coaches, the Ultimate 1 Percent. [http://r20.rs6.net=
